The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8: General Motors (GM) has formed a separate entity for sales and distribution in India as a part of a restructuring plan of the companys corporate structure. The new company, General Motors (India) Marketing Pvt Ltd, comes close on the heels of the US car major stepping up its investment in India.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8: The Reserve Bank of India has raised the limit for advance remittance for import of services to $500,000 from $100,000 without bank guarantee.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 8: Oil India Ltd expects to receive Sebi clearance for its maiden public offering within this week or the next, a top official said. Oil India will use the IPO proceeds to part-finance its Rs 4,574-crore capex plan, company chairman and managing director M.R. Pasrija said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8: SRF Ltd has completed the acquisition of Thai Baroda Industries in Rayong, Thailand. All financial dues have been paid as of this morning in Thailand, a company statement said.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8: Global rating agency Fitch said it expected oil prices to remain in the range of $50-100 per barrel despite the fall in prices in the last few weeks.                                                                                                                         
